<item>
            <title>[LU-9390] sanity test_42e: MDS BUG in kmem_cache_alloc_trace()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9390</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;andreas.dilger@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/207debbe-26b7-11e7-b742-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/207debbe-26b7-11e7-b742-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when testing patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/26750&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/26750&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_42e failed with the following error in the MDS console log:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_logs/24e7a244-26b7-11e7-b742-5254006e85c2/show_text&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_logs/24e7a244-26b7-11e7-b742-5254006e85c2/show_text&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

